x4freetext: Pd-300 Neutron Generator
The RbCl powder (99.95% pure, natural isotopic
composition, Aladdin Industrial Corporation) was put
in a sample box (material: polymethyl methacrylate).
Three samples with a diameter of 20 mm and six
monitors (niobium foil of 99.99% purity) with the
same diameter were prepared for irradiation. The RbCl
samples were 0.0672, 0.0625, and 0.0591 cm thick.
A stack of Nb-RbCl-Nb was made from these
three samples and mounted at 0, 90 and 135 deg
relative to the beam direction. The distance from
sample to detector was 0-8 cm. Samples were wrapped
in a cadmium foil in order to reduce the contribution
of thermal and epithermal effects.
High-purity germanium gamma-ray spectroscopy
(~68% relative efficiency, 1.69 keV resolution at
1332.5 keV of 60Co). The detector was coupled with a
digital gamma spectrometry system (ORTEC, model GEM
60P) and Maestro data acquisition software. The
efficiency of the detector was precalibrated using
various standard gamma sources, which were 57Co, 60Co,
F was the total correction factor of the activity,
F=fs*fc*fp. fs, fc, and fp are the correction
factors for the self-absorption of the sample at a
given gamma energy; the coincidence sum effect of
cascade gamma rays in the investigated nuclide
(84m,gRb); the attenuation of gamma rays in
polymethyl methacrylate (for niobium foil, fp = 1).
Correction factors for the self-absorption:
Samples thickness h (cm)
The total uncertainty 5.7-9.6%
Counting statistics 0.2-3.3%
Photopeak detection efficiency 2.0-3.0%
Relative gamma-ray intensity 0.04-4.8%
Half-life 0.1-0.3%
Sample weight <0.1%
Timing <1.0%
Self-absorption of gamma-ray about 0.5%
Isotopic abundance <0.1%
Cross section of the monitor reaction 1.1-
